7.	Planned Changes to Improve Safety
IKI Manufacturing expects to improve safety performance by emphasizing all elements of its PSM/RMP program. All recommendations during the Process Hazard Analysis were designed to improve the safety performance of the ammonia refrigeration process. IKI Manufacturing expects to evaluate each PHA and compliance audit recommendation in a timely manner and implement, as soon as possible, those recommendations that will reduce the possibility of a release and/or mitigate the consequences of an unintentional release.

The facility has an emergency action plan that addresses the response necessary for an accidental release of a regulated substance. The process area where filling occurs is provided with a detection system. The processes are designed so that major components can be isolated by closing selected valves. Further, operators have been trained and are knowledgeable in the safe operation of the processes. In case of a release that could travel off the property, calls would be made to the appropriate local and regional responding agencies to assist in the response. Other state and federal notifications would be made as required.

5.	Five Year Accident History
There have been no reportable releases of any regulated substance in the past five years.

6.	Emergency Response Program
This aerosols manufacturing facility has procedures in place to respond to the release of a hazardous substance. Employees are trained to evacuate their respective areas in accordance with OSHA 1910.38(a). IKI Manufacturing has also trained personnel in the Hazardous Waste Operation and Emergency Response Program, OSHA 29 CFR 1910.120 HAZWOPER. The trained personnel have been trained to the Technician Level Responder. The trained personnel will assess each release situation and determine by the risk assessment, the appropriate emergency response to initiate. 1.	Accidental Release Prevention and Emergency Response Policies
IKI Manufacturing takes many precautions to prevent or minimize accidental releases of regulated flammable substances. These precautions include safety controls (detection systems, overpressure protection devices, and automatic shutdown devices) which are designed to identify and prevent potentially unsafe conditions like pressure increases that could cause a system failure. A preventive maintenance program designed to maintain the on-going integrity of the processes is in place, in addition to a training program designed to ensure that the processes are operated by qualified personnel. All employees are informed of hazards in the workplace. Employees who work with potentially hazardous substances receive proper training in the handling of those substances. This facility has procedures in place to safely remove employees from areas in the unlikely event that a hazardous substance release was to occur, and to put in place emergency notification and response procedures.

2.	Facility and Regulated Substances
IKI Manufacturing, located in Edgerton, WI, is an aerosols manufacturing facility. The regulated substances at this facility are flammable vapors at atmospheric pressure but are kept liquified under pressure in multiple vessels located on a tank farm on the facility grounds. The regulated substances are used as propellants during the manufacturing of various aerosol products. In order to protect its employees, the public, and the environment, an integrated safety management program has been established to prevent releases and mitigate the consequences of a release, should one occur.

3.	Worst Case and Alternative Case Release Scenarios
Off Site Consequence (OCA) data is available for review onsite at the IKI Manufacturing facility.
